them know the problem. I always, ALWAYS read the bill I receive at check-out thoroughly before leaving. Mistakes can be made &amp; they probably will from time to time. Just make sure you get everything in writing. Also, keep ALL your receipts, etc., until you receive your credit card statement with all the charges on there. It is easier to dispute things. I believe this person stated they had to use their credit card in regards to the $200 refund? THAT is a good thing! You now have proof to make your case for getting it taken off of your credit card balance! We always use our credit card for airline tix, car rental, hotels, restaurants. This way, if there is a problem, it is easier to make your case. Also, always take a copy of your itinerary for EVERYTHING!*The bathroom leaves a bit to be desired! The shower stall-AND I use the term 'stall' litely!!!-had no shelf to put your soap, etc, on. I really didn't think there was a sink in the room! But, I opened a set of louvered doors &amp; there it was! Plenty of space! It was kind of cool!We didn't even have to pay for parking! We parked our car on the side street &amp; didn't have to worry! The lobby of this hotel is absolutely gorgeous! The fireplace is great! 2 comfy sofas to sit on &amp; read a good book or the paper.There is a table with chairs around it &amp; the area for the internet is nice &amp; secluded. We didn't use the internet because of the cost. I would have only emailed our daughter, anyway. No business needs.Yes, they only have coffee, juice &amp; pastries, but all of it was good. We liked being able to take our drinks with us. Whenever we would leave we were greeted. Whenever we returned we were greeted. Always making the effort to make us feel at home.This is a great location in regards to Chinatown-you are 2 blocks from Chinatown gate. The cable car stop is within a block. I had no problem with cleanliness in any part of this hotel. I am very honest with my reviews because I would want honesty returned to me in my search for hotels, restaurants, etc.Give this hotel a chance. It is a nice place for a short visit. If you don't mind small rooms, it is a great place for any kind of visit!Happy Travels!	
