Apr 28 2007	Great location - Nice hotel for the price	We stayed at the Executive for seven nights while on holiday in SF. A bit concerned by some of the reviews, I was prepared to check into another property if things weren't feeling right after the first night. To my great surprise, the Executive ended up exceeding my expectations and we really really enjoyed our stay. This is a boutique style hotel and really isn't in the same category as bigger hotels like Crowne Plaza, Hilton, Hyatt, Sheraton, etc. Boutiques typically have smaller rooms, have a smaller number of guest rooms, and in my opinion, are more charming and quaint. The rooms are small; however, not so small that we couldn't manage our two over sized pieces of luggage and all of their contents. The beds are a bit on the hard sized if you compare them to some of the upgrades that Sheraton / Hyatt etc have done the past few years; however, I slept incredibly well every night. The shower w/ bathtub and toilet are housed in a normal looking bathroom w/ door, while the sink/vanity/mirror are are positioned in a little closet. in the room. It's quite charming and worked well for us. The vanity has a hair dryer per usual, and the bathroom comes with some standard shampoos and soaps. The TVs have been upgraded--as ours was a flat screen. The alarm clock has also been upgraded recently--as ours had an ipod adaptor (which we actually used to play music throughout our stay).The hotel seemed very full--and all of the guests (ranging in age from retired to families, to business, to mid-twenties) seemed quite happy. Speaking of happy, the &quot;happy hour&quot; complimentary wine service from 5-6 was a nice touch. I met many of the other guests this way; however, only made it for wine twice. The morning breakfast consisted of coffee and orange juice w/ muffins and pastries. The location is great for getting around SF. There is a little wine/grocery store across the street which has soft drinks, wine and food to keep your late evening snacking needs fulfilled. The Powell Street Bart and MUNI and F Line are all a few blocks away which will take you all over the city, and if you're up for the touristy cable car, there are ample stops just steps away from the hotel.	
Apr 18 2007 	Perfectly Acceptable Hotel	Due to the negative comments I had read I was more than a little nervous about our stay.This is just an example of why User ratings on Internet sites need to be taken with a grain (or tablespoon) of salt.It is probably more of a 2.5 Star than a 3 Star Hotel but for a price of under $150 for a King in central San Francisco it is hard to beat.As for our overall experience rating I would lean towards giving it a 3.5 dot rating not a 4 dot rating.ROOM:The room we stayed in was probably the largest room we have had in San Francisco. It wasn't huge or anything but probably bigger than our rooms at Harbor Court or the Juliana.Besides this is San Francisco who plans on staying in the room for very long?The room was clean although the wall paper was a little old. The bathroom is a bit small and Spartan but still clean and functional.It is an old building and there is a slight musty smell. It's just old building smell really. Hardly noticed it after awhile.The biggest disappointment was the hot water in the shower in the morning. There wasn't a lot.LOCATION:The location is great. Easy walking distance through Chinatown to Washington Square and Fisherman's Wharf. Short walk to the Powell Street Muni Station just past Union Square.STAFF:The Hotel staff was very friendly and efficient. Extra towels were provided promptly. I must have mentioned, at some point in the booking process, that this was an anniversary trip. When we got to the room there was a complimentary bottle of wine and a card. I am fairly familiar with the city and had ideas on what to see and where to eat. What few city questions I posed to the concierge were answered very informatively.NOISE:Very EARLY on Monday Morning I remembered the garbage collection on Bush Street. It is loud and seems to start VERY early in the morning. You can't blame the hotel for this and I have had the same problem in other nearby hotels.DINING:We didn't eat at Masas but it looks wonderful and also amazingly expensive. EXTRAS:The complimentary newspaper was the Chronicle and not USA Today -- a definite plus. The wine at the tasting was fine and easy to quaff. The breakfast seemed sparse but we were on our way to Mamas on Washington Square anyway.PARKING: San Francisco is such a great town for walking we never get a car. Walking on Lombard in the Marina district, towards the Presidio, we noticed a lot of Motels....WHAT IT IS NOT:If I was in town on business I would probably choose a different Hotel. We were on vacation and didn't bring our laptops so I cannot speak about the wireless connection. It did not have a business center nor an exercise room. The computer in the lobby was 15 cents a minute so it could get costly. It was fine for on-line airline check-in.Also it is not a hotel to plan on spending a lot of time in the room. There is no room service and the desk is small.WHAT IT IS:A perfectly acceptable and affordable hotel for a nice weekend vacation in San Francisco.	
Feb 16 2007	Quaint nice experience.	My wife &amp; I stayed in this glorious city a while back. SF is expensive, but we found this little hotel in a super location for a very reasonable price. By no means is it a 5-star hotel, but the room was clean, nice &amp; well-appointed with quaint charm, despite being a bit small. Regardless of that, the staff was very helpful. I particularly enjoyed the wine-tasting evenings &amp; the helpful, polite front desk.Overall, I'd recommend this place for singles or couples, but for children present, you probably need a bit bigger room. For the location &amp; proximity to everything (including a marvelous little Mexican restaurant around the corner), you can't beat this place for the price. SF is a magical city with plenty of things to do, so I'd recommend just crashing here &amp; seeing the wonderful surroundings more than hanging out in a room all day.Would recommend again for a getaway for 2, but not for families because of the room size.	
